      {
        "id": "NzmVxqVyvYNvolRZ",
        "title": "Text 66",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Each student claims that the scale factor from <em>P</em> to the sketched parallelogram is 4. Are any of the students correct in their reasoning?</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "pDBahSOOC_8rwwrj",
        "title": "Text 68",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Jeff is correct in his reasoning. When a scale factor is applied in a figure, it is applied to lengths. Jeff&#x27;s perimeter is 4 times as great as the perimeter of the original parallelogram.</p><p>Janine applied a scale factor of 1/2 and Trish applied a scale factor of 2.</p>"
          ]
